==French==
===Adjective===
'''plus'''
====Pronunciation====
*[[IPA]]: (''before a consonant'') /ply/, (''before a vowel or "[[h muet]]"'') /plys/

#[[more]], [[-er]]
#:''Ton voisin est '''plus''' moche que mon frère'' - Your neighbour is ugli[[-er|er]] than my brother

===Adverb===
'''plus'''
====Pronunciation====
*[[IPA]]: /ply/   PLU S

#[[no longer]], not ... [[any more]]
#:''Tu '''n''''existe '''plus''''' - You '''no longer''' exist ''or'' You don't exist any more

===Usage notes===
*Often the difference is hard to tell between '''''ply''''' and '''''plys'''''. But generally, if a sentence has a '''''ne''''' tucked away in it, without a ''pas'' (another negative), the meaning is ''no longer''. However, the French have a tendancy to omit the ''ne''. <!--this needs some work - I don't think it is correct - Paul G, 2005-4-25-->

===Noun===
'''plus'''  (''plural:'' '''[[pluss]]''')
# the symbol +

===Verb form===
'''plus'''

# ''first-, second-person singular indicative past historic of [[plaire]]''
# masculine plural of [[plu]] (''past participle of [[plaire]] or [[pleuvoir]]'')

